            <sense xml:id="qolase-dlgenr-1">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>a woman’s headgear</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>ויעשו להם חגורות אמר ר' אבא בר כהנא אין כת' חגורה אלא חגורות חגור חגירי חגורות איסטכיון גולין סדינים, כשם שעושין לאיש כך עושין לאשה צוצלין 
                  <app>
                     <lem>קולוסין</lem>
                     <rdg wit="#Vat1">קולסוון</rdg>
                     <rdg wit="#Vat2">לקדוסוון</rdg>
                     <rdg wit="#Ox1">קלסין</rdg>
                     <rdg wit="#V K">קולסין</rdg>
                  </app> סבכין.</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">19,6</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">176: 1</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">איסטכיון</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">סבכין</ref>
                  <cit type="translation">
                     <quote>And they made themeselves girdles (ḥagorot). R. Abba b. Kahana said: Not hagorah (a girdle) but ḥagorot is written: now ḥagorot implies shirts, robes, and linen cloaks; and just as these are made for man, so for woman are made girdles, hats, and hair nets. (Cf. Freedman / Simon I 152-153)</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">Yalq 27 [I 93: 44]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">דקיסלוון</term>)</note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note>Etymology is obscure. Appears already in Targ (e.g. 1Sam 17,5 and 38, Ez 23,24 for <term xml:lang="jpa">כובע</term>). <bibl type="modern">Levy, Targ2 364b</bibl>: Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">κόρος</term> “helmet”, but cf. <bibl type="modern">Fleischer (in Levy, Targ2 576a)</bibl> and <bibl type="modern">Fränkel, AF 54</bibl>, who suggest Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">κώνος</term> as etymological source. Cf. also <bibl type="modern">Krauss, LW II 507</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">קולס</term>) Lat. galea “helmet”; <bibl type="modern">Jastrow II 1329a</bibl> “turban, head-dress“ Hebr. <term xml:lang="jpa">קלס</term>  “to be round”. Acc. to <bibl type="modern">Levy IV 262b</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">קולסיתא</term>) related to <term xml:lang="jpa">קולס</term> <term xml:lang="fjb">qwls</term> <term xml:lang="rabbinic">qolas</term> Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">καυλός</term> “stem (of a plant)” (cf. <bibl type="modern">Heijmanns [2013] 190</bibl>).</note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl>
                  <title>Sokoloff, DJPA 546b</title>
                  <citedRange>546b</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
